Cyprus Plans to Cut 218 Public-Service Jobs, Stockwatch Reports

-- B y   S t e l i o s   O r p h a n i d e s
-- 
2011-05-25T11:27:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/cyprus-plans-to-cut-218-public-service-jobs-stockwatch-reports.html
Cyprus’s government plans to cut 218
jobs in government ministries, to save 8.1 million euros ($11.4
million) a year,  Stockwatch  reported today, citing a draft bill.  The island’s  Ministry of Finance  estimates the overall
number of permanent public-sector jobs at 38,898, of which 4,945
are currently not filled, while the number of contract public
employees is 4,245, the website reported, citing the government
bill.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stelios Orphanides in Nicosia at  sorphanides@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  